    "content_hash": "1e76501ac91abb02",
    "department": "Growth",
    "description": "ABOUT SUNO\n\nWe're building the world's first platform for creating and discovering original music, including Suno Studio, a generative audio workstation, and Hooks, a new way to create and share videos that bring songs to life.\n\nPowered by the leading music-creation model and designed to amplify imagination, our platform makes it possible for anyone to turn inspiration into music. With Suno, ideas flow into sound, songs become yours, and everyone can experience the joy of creating.\n\n\nSuno is one of the fastest-growing AI startups in the world, backed by leading investors including Menlo Ventures, Lightspeed Venture Partners, Matrix, NVentures, and Hallwood Media.\n\nFounded in 2023 by Harvard alumni with a shared passion for music, Suno has empowered more than 100 million people to create original songs. In 2025, we raised a $250 million Series C to accelerate product innovation and international growth.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nWe’re looking for a Paid Social Manager who knows how to run global performance campaigns that actually convert. You’ll own our paid social channel management end-to-end — driving web and app conversions at scale across markets.\n\nThis isn’t a role for someone who follows playbooks. At Suno, we expect our team to work the way the best AI tools do — fast, smart, and always improving. You should be deeply fluent with AI, know how to build agents and automate workflows, and bring that mindset to everything you touch. If you’ve managed significant budgets across channels and geographies, understand attribution deeply, and use AI as a core part of how you work, you’ll fit right in.\n\nWe made a song about the role: https://suno.com/s/owdc28Zl5z3YqWbN\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO\n\n - Own paid social performance globally: manage campaigns across major paid social channels (Meta, TikTok, Snap, Reddit, etc.), optimizing for web and app conversions, subscriptions, and growth KPIs across multiple geographies and markets\n\n - Drive full-funnel results: manage budgets, bidding strategies, audience segmentation, and creative testing to consistently hit CPA and ROAS targets at scale\n\n - Expand and diversify our channel mix: evaluate and activate new platforms and formats as the business grows, bringing rigor and structure to how we test and scale them\n\n - Navigate app campaign complexity: own tracking setup, MMP integration (Singular, AppsFlyer, Adjust, etc.), and mobile attribution nuance across platforms\n\n - Build with AI: use LLMs, Claude, and other AI tools daily to build agents, automate workflows, improve reporting, and find efficiencies that wouldn’t exist otherwise — this is core to how we expect this role to operate\n\n - Partner with creative: own all creative analysis and give structured feedback on ad creative, brief new concepts, and drive iteration based on performance data\n\n - Own budget and forecasting: manage pacing across channels and markets, proactively reallocating spend to what’s working\n\n - Communicate with clarity: translate complex campaign data into sharp insights and recommendations for cross-functional stakeholders\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\n - 2+ years managing conversion-optimized paid social campaigns (must have Meta + TikTok experience) with meaningful budget responsibility across major platforms\n\n - Strong grasp of web conversion campaigns — pixels, events, landing page performance, and full-funnel optimization\n\n - Experience running global campaigns across multiple geographies and markets\n\n - Genuinely AI-native: you use LLMs, Claude, Claude Code, and similar tools as a core part of your day-to-day workflow — not occasionally, but constantly. You should be able to build agents, write prompts, and automate workflows without needing an engineer next to you\n\n - Experience with app campaign mechanics and mobile attribution (MMPs like Singular, AppsFlyer, Adjust; SKAdNetwork, postbacks, etc.)\n\n - Data-driven with strong analytical instincts: you build your own reports, diagnose underperformance fast, and communicate findings clearly\n\n - Comfortable operating in a fast-moving environment where channels, tools, and strategy evolve constantly\n\n - Nice to have: experience across a broad range of paid channels beyond the major social platforms\n\n\nADDITIONAL NOTES:\n\nApplicants must be eligible to work in the US.\n\n\nCOMPENSATION\n\n$110,000 – $140,000 base salary (before equity)\n\n\nPERKS \u0026 BENEFITS FOR FULL-TIME EMPLOYEES\n\n - Generous Company Equity Package\n\n - 401(k) with 3% Employer Match \u0026 Roth 401(k)\n\n - Unlimited PTO \u0026 Sick Time\n\n - Medical, Dental, \u0026 Vision Insurance (PPO w/ HSA \u0026 FSA options)\n\n - Continued / Creative Education Stipend\n\n - Generous Commuter Allowance\n\n - Free In-Office Lunch Delivery (4 Days per Week)\n\nSuno is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer. We consider qualified applicants without regard to race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, marital or family status, disability, genetic information, veteran status, or any other legally protected basis under provincial, federal, state, and local laws, regulations, or ordinances. We will also consider qualified applicants with criminal histories in a manner consistent with the requirements of state and local laws, including the Massachusetts Fair Chance in Employment Act, NYC Fair Chance Act, LA City Fair Chance Ordinance, and San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance.",
